Singleton ensures only one instance of a class exists globally with lazy initialization. Use it when you need controlled access, lazy loading, or thread-safe initialization that static exports don't provide.

```typescript
class Database {
  private static instance: Database;
  private constructor() {}
  static getInstance(): Database {
    if (!this.instance) {
