### Factory vs Abstract Factory

Factory creates single product types, Abstract Factory creates families of related products. Use Factory for simple object creation, Abstract Factory when you need coordinated creation of multiple related objects.

```typescript
// Factory: single product
class ButtonFactory {
  static create(type: 'ios' | 'android') {
    return type === 'ios' ? new IosButton() : new AndroidButton();
  }
}
// Abstract Factory: product families
interface UIFactory {
  createButton(): Button;
  createInput(): Input;
}
class IosFactory implements UIFactory {
  createButton() { return new IosButton(); }
  createInput() { return new IosInput(); }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing them as the same pattern—Abstract Factory coordinates multiple products.

