### Prototype Pattern

Prototype creates new objects by cloning an existing instance rather than creating from scratch. It's faster than construction when object creation is expensive and allows variation through cloning.

```typescript
interface Cloneable {
  clone(): this;
}
class User implements Cloneable {
  constructor(public name: string, public settings: {}) {}
  clone(): this {
    return Object.assign(Object.create(Object.getPrototypeOf(this)), this);
  }
}
const user1 = new User('John', { theme: 'dark' });
const user2 = user1.clone();
user2.name = 'Jane'; // Only user2 affected
```

**Common interview trap:** Shallow clone copies nested objects by reference—use `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify())` for deep cloning.

