### Factory vs Abstract Factory

Factory creates single product types, while Abstract Factory creates families of related products. Use Factory for simple object creation; use Abstract Factory when you need to ensure consistency across multiple related product types (e.g., different UI themes or database drivers).

```typescript
// Factory - single product
class CarFactory {
  static createCar(type: string) {
    return type === 'sedan' ? new Sedan() : new SUV();
  }
}

