### Decorator Pattern: Composition Over Inheritance

Decorator wraps an object to add behavior dynamically without modifying its structure. Unlike inheritance, it allows combining multiple features at runtime through composition, avoiding the fragile base class problem and class explosion.

```typescript
class Coffee {
  cost(): number { return 5; }
}

class MilkDecorator {
  constructor(private coffee: Coffee) {}
  cost(): number { return this.coffee.cost() + 2; }
}

const drink = new MilkDecorator(new Coffee());
console.log(drink.cost()); // 7
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing Decorator with simple wrapper functions; Decorator maintains the interface while adding responsibilities.

