answer.en:
### Observer Pattern: Event-Driven Architecture

Observer establishes a one-to-many dependency where multiple observers subscribe to state changes. To prevent memory leaks, always unsubscribe observers when they're no longer needed, typically using a cleanup function or WeakMap for weak references.

```typescript
class Subject {
  private observers = new Set<(data: any) => void>();
  subscribe(observer: (data: any) => void) { this.observers.add(observer); }
  unsubscribe(observer: (data: any) => void) { this.observers.delete(observer); }
  notify(data: any) { this.observers.forEach(obs => obs(data)); }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Forgetting to implement unsubscribe method, leading to dangling references and memory leaks in long-lived applications.

