### Bridge vs Adapter: Different Intents

Adapter fixes incompatibility between existing interfaces after-the-fact, while Bridge decouples abstraction from implementation upfront to avoid combinatorial explosion. Bridge is superior when you have two independent hierarchies (e.g., Shape × Color) that need flexible combinations.

```typescript
interface Color { fill(): string; }
class RedColor implements Color { fill() { return 'red'; } }

abstract class Shape {
  constructor(protected color: Color) {}
  abstract draw(): string;
}

class Circle extends Shape {
  draw() { return `Circle in ${this.color.fill()}`; }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Thinking Bridge and Adapter are the same because both involve composition; Adapter is about compatibility, Bridge is about preventing design fragility.

answer.ru:
